.TH ZOPEN-CLEAN "1" "June 2026" "zopen tools 0.8.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zopen-clean \- manual page for zopen-clean 0.8.5
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zopen-clean
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR] [\fI\,PACKAGE\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
zopen\-clean is a utility for zopen community to remove uneeded resources
from the system to save space and prevent clutter.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-deep\fR
deep clean \- run all cleanup operations
.TP
\fB\-\-all\fR
apply cleanup command to all applicable packages.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-cache\fR
[PACKAGE ...]
cleans the downloaded package cache; packages will be
re\-downloaded if needed.
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-dangling\fR
removes dangling symlinks from the zopen file system in
case of issues during package maintenance.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR, \-?
display this help and exit.
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-metadata\fR
cleans and refreshes the metadata for zopen.
.TP
\fB\-u\fR, \fB\-\-unused\fR [PACKAGE ...]
remove versions of PACKAGEs that are available as
alternatives, leaving only the currently active version.
.TP
\fB\-\-nostats\fR
do not output statistics from the clean operation(s)
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
run in verbose mode.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
print version.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
zopen clean \-c
clear the package download cache
.TP
zopen clean \-d
analyse the zopen file system and remove dangling symlinks
.TP
zopen clean \-u [PACKAGE]
remove unused versions for PACKAGE
.TP
zopen clean \-u \-\-all
remove all unused packages within the zopen environment
.IP
zopen clean \-\-deep
